CatDescriptText: Cutline of images published in the Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 13, 1954, pg. 12 reads: " Hill City Contestants For Queen - Among the organizations sponsoring some of these lovely young teenagers, who are striving to wear the Hill City Queen's crown at the may Coronation Ball, are Alpha Alpha Omega Chapter of AKA, Omicron Psi Chapter of Omega Fraternity, Hill City Women's Auxiliary, and Schenley Heights Neighborhood Club.  In this group are, left to right...Virginia Jefferson...Alma Bowles...-Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Virginia Jefferson wearing light colored neck scarf and cardigan with beaded snowflake design, posed in front of light colored background in Harris Studio for Hill City Teen Queen contest; Portrait of Alma Bowles wearing light colored shirt with double dark chain design on collar, posed in front of light colored background in Harris Studio for Hill City Teen Queen contest
